Portugal’s Cristiano Ronaldo became the first European to score 100 international goals in men’s football with a brilliant free-kick against Sweden. The captain curled a stunning effort into the top corner from 25 yards to reach the landmark. That gave Portugal a 1-0 Nations League lead in Solna at half-time. The Juve forward is within nine goals of the world-record 109 that Iran’s Ali Daei managed during his playing career. Details later…